was so with Ahab; only that now, of late, he seemed so much to live in the open 
air, that truly speaking, his visits were more to the cabin, than from the 
cabin to the planks. “It feels like going down into one’s tomb,”—he 
would mutter to himself—“for an old captain like me to be descending this 
narrow scuttle, to go to my grave-dug berth.”
